
[1]enchantment

   ENCH`ANTMENT, n. The act of producing certain wonderful effects by the
   invocation or aid of demons, or the agency of certain supposed spirits;
   the use of magic arts, spells or charms; incantation.

   The magicians of Egypt did so with their enchantments. Ex.7.

   1. Irresistible influence; overpowering influence of delight.

   The warmth of fancy--which holds the heart of a reader under the
   strongest enchantment.
